On December 21, 2009, pursuant to the terms of the previously announced Agreement and Plan of Merger, dated as of November 16, 2009, by and among Applied Materials, Inc., a Delaware corporation ("Applied"), Jupiter Acquisition Sub, Inc., a Delaware corporation and a wholly-owned subsidiary of Applied ("Acquisition Sub"), and Semitool, Inc., a Montana corporation ("Semitool"), Semitool was merged with and into Acquisition Sub (the "Merger"). Acquisition Sub was the surviving corporation in the Merger and will continue as a wholly-owned subsidiary of Applied. As a result of the Merger, each outstanding share of Semitool common stock (other than shares held by Applied, Semitool or their respective subsidiaries, or held by shareholders of Semitool who properly assert dissenters' rights under Montana law) was automatically converted into the right to receive $11.00 in cash, without interest thereon and less any required withholding tax. The Merger follows the completion of Applied's $11.00 per share cash tender offer for all outstanding shares of Semitool at 12:00 midnight, Eastern Standard Time, on December 17, 2009.
On December 21, 2009, Applied issued a press release announcing the completion of the Merger, which is filed as Exhibit 99.1 hereto and incorporated by reference herein.
 
